decades to come.

31:01.259 --> 31:07.632 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A national TV audience looked on
last night
as Judge Neil Gorsuch summed up
his judicial

31:07.666 --> 31:09.401 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
philosophy.

31:09.434 --> 31:11.169 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NEIL GORSUCH, Supreme Court
Nominee: It is
the role of judges to apply, not
alter, the

31:11.203 --> 31:12.637 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
work of the people's
representatives.

31:12.671 --> 31:18.110 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A judge who likes every outcome
he reaches
is very likely a bad judge.

31:18.143 --> 31:23.949 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: Gorsuch was
schooled at Columbia
University, obtained a Harvard
law degree,

31:23.982 --> 31:25.717 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and then a degree at Oxford.

31:25.751 --> 31:30.655 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He clerked for then-Justice
Byron White and
Justice Anthony Kennedy, who
still serves

31:30.689 --> 31:32.157 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
on the court.

31:32.190 --> 31:35.927 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And he practiced law privately
before joining
the Department of Justice.

31:35.961 --> 31:41.199 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Then, in 2006, President Bush
nominated him
to the 10th Circuit Court of
Appeals based

31:41.233 --> 31:42.367 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in Denver.

31:42.400 --> 31:45.370 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
He won unanimous Senate
confirmation.

31:45.403 --> 31:50.776 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In the decade since, Gorsuch has
made his
mark in several notable cases,
especially

31:50.809 --> 31:52.611 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
on religious liberty.

31:52.644 --> 31:58.416 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He sided with the Hobby Lobby
challenge to
Obamacare, ruling for religious
organizations

31:58.450 --> 32:01.153 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
opposing a contraceptive
mandate.

32:01.186 --> 32:06.324 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In that decision, Gorsuch, along
with two
other judges, wrote: "For some,
religion provides

32:06.358 --> 32:11.163 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
an essential source of guidance,
both about
what constitutes wrongful
conduct and the

32:11.196 --> 32:16.134 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
degree to which those who assist
others in
committing wrongful conduct
themselves bear

32:16.168 --> 32:18.170 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
moral culpability."

32:18.203 --> 32:22.774 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If confirmed, Gorsuch would fill
the seat
of the late Antonin Scalia.

32:22.808 --> 32:25.877 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Last night, Gorsuch called
Scalia a lion of
the law.

32:25.911 --> 32:32.484 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Now, at age 49, Gorsuch has a
chance to bring
that same legal philosophy to
bear for decades

32:32.517 --> 32:34.753 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
to come.

32:34.786 --> 32:39.658 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And to dig into what we know
about that legal
philosophy, we are joined by two
longtime

32:39.691 --> 32:45.197 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Supreme Court watchers, Nina
Totenberg, legal
affairs correspondent for NPR,
and Marcia

32:45.230 --> 32:50.235 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Coyle, chief Washington
correspondent for
"The National Law Journal" and a
"NewsHour"

32:50.268 --> 32:51.236 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
regular.

32:51.269 --> 32:52.237 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Thank you both for being with
us.

32:52.270 --> 32:54.072 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Nina, let's begin with you.

32:54.105 --> 32:58.710 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We will look at a landmark case,
the Hobby
Lobby case, which gets into
religious freedom,

32:58.743 --> 33:00.979 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
rights of employers vs.
employees.

33:01.012 --> 33:02.981 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That's a real shorthand version
of it.

33:03.014 --> 33:08.486 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I'm going to read you a little
passage from
a ruling that was authored by
him in a lower

33:08.520 --> 33:10.322 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
court, obviously.

33:10.355 --> 33:14.459 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
